// ERROR: E2440
// ADR-0084 §AMEND Lat B - WO Teeth 3 (move-while-borrowed). Reassigning `e`
// WHILE its payload sub-borrow `s` is still live (SAME match arm, before the
// arm's value escapes to the merge point) must be rejected -- reassigning
// `e` would free the OLD String "hi" out from under `s`.
//
// SCOPE NOTE (see WO report HONEST LIMIT): this locks the WITHIN-ARM case,
// which the borrowck DOES catch. It does NOT cover the case where the
// payload sub-borrow escapes the match (e.g. `let n = match &0 e {...};`
// then `e` is reassigned/moved AFTER the match, `n` used afterward) -- that
// broader case was probed live and found UNGUARDED (no E2440), a
// load-bearing gap reported separately. Do not read this fixture as proof
// the general move-while-borrowed hazard is closed.
enum Msg { Ping(String), Pong }
function main() -> Integer {
    let mutable e = Msg::Ping("hi");
    return match &0 e {
        Msg::Ping(s) => {
            e = Msg::Ping("bye");
            length(s)
        },
        Msg::Pong => 0,
    };
}
